Installing Wireshark
1. On Windows

Open browser → go to wireshark.org
Click Download → Windows Installer (64-bit)
Run the installer
During installation:

✅ Select Wireshark
✅ Install Npcap (mandatory for packet capture)

Click Next → Install → Finish

-> Capturing Live Network Traffic
Step 1: Open Wireshark
Launch Wireshark


Step 2: Select Network Interface

Choose:

Wi-Fi → if using wireless

Ethernet → if using LAN cable


Step 3: Start Capture

Double-click the interface


Step 4: Generate Traffic

While capture is running:
Open a website (google.com)
Ping a site:
ping google.com

Step 5: Stop Capture

-> Wireshark uses display filters to show specific packets. 
1. HTTP Packets
2. DNS Packets
3. TCP Packets
4. UDP Packets


